# SourceA ecosystem — AUTO CONFLICT RESOLUTION

**When any rules conflict → run SKILL-007 before disk edits.**

## Precedence (short)

1. **Founder current message** (`SAVE TO:`, `EDIT ALLOWED:` + `ACTION:`, `ASF:`, bounded `WORK:`)
2. **Permission / ask-first** (`001-founder-verbs`, SAVE · WORK · EDIT ALLOWED)
3. **Open P0/P1 incidents** (INCIDENT-010/011, CIR-COSPRO)
4. **`execution_authority: false`**
5. **Workflow bundles** (RESEARCH 4-step, INBOX — only after T0)
6. **Ship-first / plan.json / mandatory paste alone** — never self-start

## Hard law

> Ship-first, RESEARCH mandatory paste, and bare **save** **never** override ask-first or `001-founder-verbs`.

## Name unification (INCIDENT-025 — mandatory every session)

Before renaming or creating any **tab · category · thread · tag · link label · Hub title**:

1. **Read conversation + locked SSOT** — `rg` the proposed name and related terms across `SourceA/`.
2. **Cite existing canonical** — authority index row · `NAV_TABS` · locked doc · registry id.
3. **Never replace a registered title** with a status word (*pending*, *live*, *new*) — put status in subtitle/badge/desc only.
4. **Remind founder proactively** of related names when answering (e.g. **Advisor track** `advisor-discussion` ≠ **AI Advisory** `ai-advisory`).
5. **Hub advisor crisis table:** title **Advisor track** only · id `advisor-discussion` · doc `SOURCEA_FOUNDER_ADVISOR_DISCUSSION_TRACK_LOCKED_v1.md`.

Validator: `bash scripts/validate-hub-advisor-track-naming-v1.sh`

## On conflict

1. Stop — no edits
2. Name both rules + winner
3. Propose A/B/C
4. **ASK founder**
5. Implement only bounded T0 order

